    },
    {
      "id": 2,
      "text": "Five historic museums—Octagon House, Sims Store, Martisco Station, School House #1, and an agricultural museum—chart 207 years of Camillus growth.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        4
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 1"
      ],
      "source": "https://www.townofcamillus.gov/default.aspx?PageID=855"
    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "text": "The 1838 railroad line from Syracuse to Auburn ran through Camillus, sparking businesses that became known worldwide.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        7,
        11
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia",
        "Web source 1"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Camillus%2C_New_York"
    },
    {
      "id": 4,
      "text": "The Nine Mile Creek Aqueduct and Wilcox Octagon House are listed on the National Register of Historic Places.",
